==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lection
<hw>Lec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lectio</ets>, fr. <ets>legere</ets>, <ets>lectum</ets>, to read.
See <er>lesson</er>, <er>Legend</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A lesson or selection, especially of Scripture,
read in divine service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A reading; a variation in the text.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We ourselves are offended by the obtrusion of the new
<qex>lections</qex> into the text.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lectionary</ent>⟦br⟧
